---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import EvidenceTable from '../components/EvidenceTable.astro';

const repo = 'https://github.com/sullson/newcode-devops';
---

<Layout>
  <!-- (1) Hero -->
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h1>
        <span class="accent">Senior DevOps</span> for production AI infrastructure
      </h1>
      <p>
        I build and run production-grade <strong>Azure / AKS</strong> platforms.
        Everything below lives in this repo and actually runs — not a list of
        skills, the working proof.
      </p>

      <!-- Self-explaining live status. Server-rendered state = "asleep" (with the
           window + working links); the inline script flips it to "LIVE" if the
           on-demand cluster answers /healthz. -->
      <div
        id="live"
        class="live live--off"
        data-app="https://aks-newcode.msulawiak.pl"
      >
        <span class="live__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <p class="live__text">
          <strong>The live platform is asleep right now.</strong> The full
          private-AKS cluster — app, signed image, real metrics — runs daily
          <strong>10:00–13:00 (Europe/Warsaw)</strong>, then tears itself down so
          it costs nothing idle. Catch it in the window, or ask me to spin it up.
        </p>
        <div class="live__links cta-row">
          <a class="btn btn--primary" href="https://aks-newcode.msulawiak.pl">Live app&nbsp;↗</a>
          <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="https://grafana-newcode.msulawiak.pl">Live metrics&nbsp;↗</a>
          <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={repo}>Source code&nbsp;↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="badges">
        <span class="badge">Azure</span>
        <span class="badge">AKS</span>
        <span class="badge">Terraform</span>
        <span class="badge">Helm</span>
        <span class="badge">GitHub Actions</span>
        <span class="badge">EU / GDPR</span>
      </div>

      <script is:inline>
        // Flip the badge to "LIVE" if the on-demand AKS app answers its
        // CORS-open /healthz. One fetch to our own cluster — no framework,
        // no third party, no tracker. Off-window (or JS off) it stays "asleep".
        (function () {
          var el = document.getElementById("live");
          if (!el || !window.fetch) return;
          var ctrl = new AbortController();
          var t = setTimeout(function () { ctrl.abort(); }, 4000);
          fetch(el.dataset.app + "/healthz", { cache: "no-store", signal: ctrl.signal })
            .then(function (r) {
              clearTimeout(t);
              if (!r.ok) return;
              el.className = "live live--on";
              el.querySelector(".live__text").innerHTML =
                "<strong>LIVE right now.</strong> The private-AKS cluster is up — " +
                "the app and the metrics below are served straight from it, no login.";
            })
            .catch(function () { clearTimeout(t); });
        })();
      </script>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- (2) This site is the proof -->
  <Section id="proof" eyebrow="Not a slide deck" title="This site is the proof">
    <p class="lead">
      You're reading the always-on front (Azure Static Web Apps). The <em>same</em>
      image is deployed on demand to a real, private <strong>AKS</strong> cluster
      via Helm — that's the daily live window above.
    </p>
    <ul class="notes">
      <li>
        <strong>See it yourself in the window:</strong> the
        <a href="https://aks-newcode.msulawiak.pl">app</a> and a live
        <a href="https://grafana-newcode.msulawiak.pl">Grafana dashboard</a>
        (no login) are both served from the cluster.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Zero inbound ports.</strong> The AKS API server is private; CI
        reaches it over Tailscale, traffic arrives via an outbound-only Cloudflare
        Tunnel. Nothing is exposed to the internet.
      </li>
      <li>
        Timestamped proof of each run — cosign verify, <code>kubectl</code> output —
        is committed to <a href={`${repo}/tree/main/docs/evidence`}>docs/evidence</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={repo}>Source on GitHub</a>
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={`${repo}/tree/main/docs`}>Architecture docs</a>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- (3) JD-to-evidence mapping -->
  <Section
    id="evidence"
    eyebrow="Newcode.ai job requirements"
    title="Every requirement, mapped to working code"
  >
    <p class="lead" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">
      No claims without a file. Each line below links to the exact artifact in
      this repo that backs it.
    </p>
    <EvidenceTable />
  </Section>

  <!-- (3b) Track record -->
  <Section
    id="background"
    eyebrow="15+ years in production infrastructure"
    title="Track record"
  >
    <ul class="notes">
      <li>
        <strong>AI Delivery Lead, Sky.</strong> Led delivery of a governed, multi-tenant agentic-AI
        platform — security gateway, sandboxed agent runtime, approval-aware tool registry and RAG —
        across Azure, AWS and GCP, and industrialised AI across the software-delivery lifecycle.
        <span class="plain">A company can put AI agents to real work safely — with approvals, an audit trail and cost control built in, not bolted on later.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Senior Azure Architect &amp; DevOps, PwC.</strong> Built and optimised Azure DevOps
        CI/CD with FinOps and on-demand AKS, pipeline templates and automated secret rotation; audited
        an enterprise platform on AKS / Terraform / GitOps; led Microsoft-stack upskilling for a large
        engineering group.
        <span class="plain">Software ships faster and cheaper, breaks less often, and the team can keep it that way.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Lead Azure Architect &amp; DevOps, Lingaro.</strong> Azure DevOps + Terraform CI/CD,
        AKS and Ansible at scale — high-availability clusters and fast, repeatable deployments.
        <span class="plain">Systems that stay online and roll out updates in minutes instead of days.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        Earlier: infrastructure architecture and systems administration across many SMEs
        (Linux/Windows, virtualization, DR). MSc Robotics.
        <strong>Microsoft Certified: Azure Solutions Architect Expert.</strong>
        <span class="plain">Years of keeping real business systems running, fast and recoverable.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <!-- (3c) Independent delivery -->
  <Section
    id="independent"
    eyebrow="A dozen-plus smaller companies"
    title="Independent delivery"
  >
    <p class="lead" style="margin-bottom:1.25rem">
      Alongside contracting, I've delivered automation and platform work for a dozen-plus smaller
      companies — software houses, businesses automating their operations, IT product teams, and my
      own back office. A few representative builds:
    </p>
    <ul class="notes">
      <li>
        <strong>Multi-agent AI delivery platform</strong> — an orchestrator spawning ephemeral agent
        containers, with all side-effects routed through an authenticated, audited gateway (per-caller
        allow-lists, network-isolated egress); plus a GitHub-driven agent crew (Planner / Developer /
        Reviewer) that runs Issue → PR → merge.
        <span class="plain">Routine coding and ops get done by AI on their own — with a human signing off the important moves.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>AI product stack</strong> — chatbot, RAG connectors, MCP integrations and a Teams-RAG
        assistant, packaged for repeatable deployment.
        <span class="plain">A company can ask its own documents and data questions and get straight answers, instead of digging by hand.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>GPU inference service</strong> — audio/video transcription with speaker diarization
        (Whisper / NeMo), GPU images built and shipped through GitHub Actions.
        <span class="plain">Hours of audio and video turn into accurate, speaker-labelled text automatically.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Bare-metal GPU server, deployed and AI-operated end to end</strong> — a dual-Blackwell
        box (2× RTX 6000 Pro / 192 GB VRAM, 64-core Threadripper, ECC RAM, ZFS NVMe) on Proxmox with
        VFIO GPU passthrough, NVIDIA / CUDA and a container GPU runtime, Tailscale-only access and
        Cloudflare-Tunnel ingress — provisioned by Ansible + GitHub Actions and managed through an AI
        ops workflow.
        <span class="plain">A company's own private AI supercomputer — powerful, fully under its control, and kept running for it.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Product apps with full CI/CD</strong> — e.g. an OCR-based invoicing/accounting app
        (Next.js, PostgreSQL, object storage, job queue) on a containerized deploy pipeline.
        <span class="plain">Boring paperwork — like reading and filing invoices — handled automatically.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Infrastructure tooling</strong> — GitOps VM-fleet automation (Ansible + GitHub Actions
        over Tailscale) and a Terraform-managed edge (Cloudflare DNS / WAF / origin certs / Zero-Trust
        tunnels in front of an NGINX reverse proxy).
        <span class="plain">New servers and websites go live safely in minutes, with nothing done by hand.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <!-- (4) Security posture -->
  <Section
    id="security"
    eyebrow="Built for confidential client data"
    title="Zero secrets in a public repo"
  >
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>OIDC, not stored keys</h3>
        <p>
          Azure auth uses GitHub workload-identity federation. No service-principal
          secrets exist anywhere in the repo or CI.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Key Vault + CSI</h3>
        <p>
          In-cluster secrets (e.g. the tunnel token) flow from Azure Key Vault via
          the Secrets Store CSI Driver and Workload Identity — never committed.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Secret scanning as a gate</h3>
        <p>
          gitleaks runs pre-commit and in CI. A leaked value fails the build,
          not production.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Signed, scanned images</h3>
        <p>
          Trivy blocks HIGH/CRITICAL CVEs; cosign keyless signs every image and
          deploys verify the signature.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
      <a class="btn btn--ghost" href={`${repo}/blob/main/SECURITY.md`}>Read SECURITY.md</a>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- (5) Contact / CTA -->
  <Section id="contact" eyebrow="Engagement" title="Let's talk">
    <p class="lead">
      From an empty subscription to a signed, monitored, multi-tenant AKS
      platform — built, deployed and observed by the pipelines in this repo. If
      that's the kind of infrastructure you need, let's talk.
    </p>
    <ul class="notes" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem">
      <li>LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/michal-sulawiak">michal-sulawiak</a></li>
      <li>Code: <a href={repo}>{repo.replace('https://', '')}</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="cta-row">
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href={repo}>
        Browse the full repo
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <footer class="site">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>
        Built and operated by Michał Sulawiak — the infrastructure
        is the CV.
      </span>
      <span class="mono">newcode.msulawiak.pl</span>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
